race.description: Australia Day Races At The Mtc Maiden Handicap
race.comment: UNDER WRAPS (6) is an Astern gelding on debut for the Beasley camp who impressed in his recent trial win when cruising stylishly to the line. With the red-hot Boudvillain booked, he looks ready to kick things off with a bang. RUM JUNGLE (5) continues to chase that elusive maiden victory but has been honest, placing in four of six starts. Has the pace to offset a wide alley and is sure to give backers another bold sight. FORREST DANCER (4) is a Tagaloa gelding on debut for the Spackman camp. Has shown encouraging signs in his trials, particularly the latest when lengthening nicely under his own esteem. Draws to get the gun run for Guymer and can make a winning start. BURNT TO A CRISP (1) is another debutant who has caught the eye in his lead-up work and is worth keeping safe.
